#####Sun
The Sun is the star at the center of the Solar System. It is by far the largest object in the Solar System and consists of hot plasma, which generates a magnetic field that extends to Earth. The Sun is divided into eight regions called solar panels, which are filled with sunspots. These panels are held together by a gravitational force generated from the core. The energy produced by the sun is made up of the proton-proton cycle, where two protons are joined together to form a deuterium atom, while releasing an electron; in a follow-up reaction, a helium nucleus (a positively charged alpha particle) is formed, along with a free neutron. This second stage is what causes the sun's brightness, as it releases a gamma ray photon in the process. When this happens, a little bit of the sun is turned into nuclear ash.

The outer region of the sun is called the corona, which is the highest temperature in the Solar System, reaching a maximum of 2 million degrees Celsius. The surface temperature of the sun is approximately 5,500 degrees C
